The paper deals with the Constraint Satisfaction Problem (CSP) and its connection to descriptive complexity theory. The main result involves proving the 2-Helly property for coset templates, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses algorithms for solving CSP, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of fixed-point logics and connections to CFI graphs suggest a connection to logic and model theory (cs.LO). The paper also mentions bounded width, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the use of group actions and majority polymorphisms suggests a connection to graph theory (cs.GT).
